  "query": "2026 Florida Republican gubernatorial primary status: Byron Donalds candidacy, opponents, Trump endorsement, polling, competitors dropping out. Who is running against Donalds and what are the polls showing as of mid-2026?",
  "answer": "I've completed the research on the 2026 Florida Republican gubernatorial primary. Here's the summary:\n\n**Byron Donalds is the dominant, Trump-endorsed frontrunner** as of mid-July 2026:\n\n- **Trump endorsement**: Full/early endorsement (Feb 2025), tied to the Trump–DeSantis rivalry\n- **Fundraising**: Reportedly $81M+\n- **Polling**: Leads by 40+ points in every credible poll. Most recent detailed poll (AIF, June 3–7): **Donalds 54%**, Fishback 8%, Collins 5%, Renner 2%, undecided 31%\n- **Prediction markets**: Polymarket implies **~96%** he wins the nomination\n\n**Who's running against him** (all in single digits):\n1. **Jay Collins** — Lt. Governor (former Green Beret)\n2. **James Fishback** — investor/newcomer\n3. **Paul Renner** — former FL House Speaker\n\n**Key context:**\n- **Casey DeSantis never entered** — she was long speculated but appears only in *hypothetical* poll matchups (one UNF outlier had her narrowly leading Donalds in a hypothetical field). She is not a candidate.\n- **Field consolidating around Donalds**: DeSantis allies broke away to endorse him on July 6, 2026.\n- **Active litigation**: Collins is suing to remove Fishback from the ballot over a residency requirement; hearing set for July 21, 2026.\n- Primary is **August 18, 2026**; general **November 3, 2026** (rated Solid Republican).\n\nFull structured findings with all data points and sources have been submitted.",
